                         <div aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-2041" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="1" hidden="false" id="elementor-tab-content-2041" role="tabpanel" tabindex="0">
                          <p>
                           This program serves all Land Grant Universities in the United States and is in partnership with Oklahoma State University. Funding is made possible through a cooperative agreement with USDA-NIFA, grant no. 2020-41595-30123
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           Through New Technologies for Ag Extension (NTAE),
                           <a href="http://extension.org/ntae" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            Cooperative Extension programs
                           </a>
                           have the opportunity to work with the Extension Foundation for one year to receive support services including partnership development, market research, professional development, leadership development, publishing support, and more. Our next nomination for 2021-2022 projects will begin in Spring 2021. Please check back for updates.
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           Additionally, this program funds national tools for Cooperative Extension such as
                           <a href="http://ask2.extension.org" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            Ask Extension
                           </a>
                           and
                           <a href="http://connect.extension.org" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            Connect Extension.
                            <br/>
                           </a>
                          </p>
                          <p style="text-align: center;">
                           <a href="https://extension.org" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            <button>
                             2021-2022 NTAE Nominations (Coming Soon!)
                            </button>
                           </a>
                          </p>
                         </div>
                         <div aria-controls="elementor-tab-content-2042" aria-expanded="false" aria-selected="false" class="elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title" data-tab="2" role="tab" tabindex="-1">
                          Pesticide Safety Education Funds Management Program (PSEFMP)

                         <div aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-2042" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="2" hidden="hidden" id="elementor-tab-content-2042" role="tabpanel" tabindex="0">
                          <p>
                           We are pleased to have received a funding opportunity for Land Grant University Pesticide Safety Education Programs (PSEP). This opportunity is made available through a cooperative agreement (#X8-83698001) with the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to establish and administer a national sub-award program in support of pesticide applicator education, and training for certified applicators of restricted used pesticides.
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           The
                           <a href="http://npsec.us/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            National Pesticide Safety Education Center (NPSEC)
                           </a>
                           will continue to collaborate with the Extension Foundation to lead the professional development part of the project and to assist PSEPs in enhancing some of the educational products they develop as part of the expectations attached to the funding.

                           <br/>
                          </p>

                          <h4>
                           Innovation Services
                          </h4>
                          The Impact Collaborative is a bundle of services and events that are funded by and for our members only.
                          <p style="text-align: left;">
                           <span style="font-weight: 400;">
                            It is a place where Extension programs from across the country come to take a deep dive into their project and program planning using our innovation skill-building tools we’ve developed over the past five years. We connect those teams with subject matter experts in a variety of fields to help fill gaps in their project and program planning, and we train people in our innovation skill-building methodology so they can use the methodology and those skills to catalyze innovation with Extension programs locally.
                           </span>
                          </p>
                          <span style="font-weight: 400;">
                           This Impact Collaborative program combines
                          </span>
                          <b>
                           creative entrepreneurial methodology
                          </b>
                          <span style="font-weight: 400;">
                           with
                          </span>
                          <b>
                           Cooperative Extension best practices
                          </b>
                          <span style="font-weight: 400;">
                           .
                          </span>
                          <p style="text-align: center;">
                           <a href="https://connect.extension.org/calendar/extension-foundation-member-calendar" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            <button>
                             Impact Collaborative Offerings
                            </button>
                           </a>
                          </p>
                          <h4>
                          </h4>
                          <h4 class="ct-heading-tag">
                           Leadership Development for Extension Foundation Members &amp; Their Teams
                          </h4>
                          Friction happens when people don’t understand one another. Confusion happens as a result of poor communication. Underperformance happens when people aren’t engaged.

We are currently working with 15 institutions at the 1890 Extension Leadership Academy and
                          <em>
                           New Technologies for Ag Extensio
                          </em>
                          n project teams in these capacities.

Each of our offerings focus on behavior changes that will help you realize your potential.
                          <p style="text-align: center;">
                           <a href="https://extension.org/leadership" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
                            <button>
                             Impact Collaborative Leadership Development
                            </button>
                           </a>
                          </p>
                         </div>
                         <div aria-controls="elementor-tab-content-2044" aria-expanded="false" aria-selected="false" class="elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title" data-tab="4" role="tab" tabindex="-1">
                          1890 Extension Leadership Academy
                         </div>
                         <div aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-2044" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="4" hidden="hidden" id="elementor-tab-content-2044" role="tabpanel" tabindex="0">
                          <p>
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           <img alt="" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-20514" height="120" loading="lazy" src="https://149405714.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/1890-ELA.png" width="180"/>
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           <span style="font-weight: 400;">
                            Since 2018, the Extension Foundation is proud to partner with Fort Valley State University to present the 1890s Extension Leadership Academy.  We work closely with partners from Fort Valley State University, Kentucky State University, and Lincoln University to make this possible.
                           </span>
                          </p>
                          <p>
                           The purpose of the 1890 Extension Leadership Academy is to prepare future and upcoming leaders in Extension to act as change agents to create a culture that encourages and sustains innovation throughout the organization. By building the capacity of these leaders, they will be capable of taking on 1890 issues so that the system will have the agility to address other opportunities and challenges proactively.
                          </p>
